4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, individuals retired under
6 the Employees' Retirement System may return to work in
7 a part-time capacity without suspension of his or her
8 retirement allowance, provided the individual is
9 subject to an annual earning limit.
10 This bill would authorize any individual who has
11 been retired under the Employees' Retirement System or
12 the Teachers' Retirement System for at least 12 months
13 to return to work for either system without suspension
14 of his or her retirement benefits, with no regard for
15 the annual earning limit, but would prohibit the
16 individual from accruing additional retirement
17 benefits.
18 This bill would provide that such an individual
19 must commit to employment for three consecutive years.
20 This bill would also require the Board of
21 Control to establish a percentage of earnable
22 compensation that each individual returning to work
23 pursuant to this bill must pay to support the
24 administration of the retirement system.
