TO BE ENTITLED
HB470 INTRODUCED
29 AN ACT
30
31 Relating to retired state employees; to authorize
32 certain retired state employees to return to work, subject to
33 certain conditions; and to require the Board of Control to
34 establish a percentage which such employees must pay to
35 support the administration of the retirement system.
36 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
37 Section 1. Section 36-27-8.2, Code of Alabama 1975, as
38 last amended by Act 2025-409, 2025 Regular Session, is amended
39 to read as follows:
40 "§36-27-8.2
41 (a) Any individual who is retired under the Employees'
42 Retirement System may perform duties in any capacity,
43 including as an independent contractor, with any employer
44 participating in the Employees' Retirement System or the
45 Teachers' Retirement System without suspension of his or her
46 retirement allowance provided that: (i) the individual is not
47 employed in a permanent full-time capacity; and (ii) the
48 individual's compensation from the employer in calendar year
49 2016 does not exceed thirty thousand dollars ($30,000).
50 Beginning in calendar year 2017, and each calendar year
51 thereafter, the annual earning limit shall be increased by the
52 same percentage increase as the increase in the Consumer Price
53 Index for all urban consumers as published by the U.S.
54 Department of Labor, Bureau of Labor Statistics. Any increase
55 in the annual earning limit shall be rounded to the next
56 lowest multiple of one thousand dollars ($1,000) with any
Page 2

lowest multiple of one thousand dollars ($1,000) with any
