57 amount in excess of the one thousand dollar ($1,000) multiple
58 considered in determining the increase for the following year.
59 Each adjustment shall be based on the increase in the index
60 for the preceding 12-month period ending on September 30 and
61 the increase shall be effective for the following calendar
62 year.
63 (b)(1) Any individual who is retired under the
64 Employees' Retirement System or Teachers' Retirement System
65 may perform duties in any capacity, including as an
66 independent contractor, with any employer participating in the
67 Employees' Retirement System or the Teachers' Retirement
68 System without suspension of his or her retirement benefits
69 and without regard for the annual earning limit described in
70 subsection (a), provided that the individual meets all of the
71 following criteria:
72 a. The individual has drawn his or her retirement
73 benefit for 12 consecutive months.
74 b. The individual commits to working for that employer
75 for three consecutive years.
76 c. The individual pays an amount equal to a specified
77 percentage of the individual's earnable compensation to
78 support the administrative expenses of the retirement system.
79 The percentage rate shall be fixed by the Board of Control and
80 may not be recouped to the individual.
81 (2) An individual employed pursuant to this section may
82 not participate in or accrue additional benefits under the
83 Employees' Retirement System or the Teachers' Retirement
84 System for that service.
